  "summary": "Malicious code in rollup-plugin-polyfill-helper (npm)",
  "details": "Rollup-plugin-polyfill-helper is a combosquat package impersonating a rollup polyfill plugin. When required, it fetches JavaScript payloads from rest-icon-helper[.]store (paths /icons/303 and /icons/389) and executes them via eval(JSON.parse(body)), giving the remote server full control over the runtime. The package exports getPlugin(), setPlugin(), and getPluginExten() functions that perform this fetch-and-eval with retry logic. On non-Windows systems the first payload runs immediately and a second is scheduled 60 seconds later; on Windows the second payload runs directly. The package has no actual rollup plugin interface and no repository.",
